SYSTEM OVERVIEW

System: Multi-tenant SaaS backend
Architecture: Modular monolith (logical services)
Communication: REST (external), gRPC (internal)
Storage: PostgreSQL + MinIO

TRUST LEVEL DEFINITIONS

Untrusted → Fully attacker-controlled

Partially Trusted → Validated identity but user-controlled intent

Trusted Internal → Server-controlled logic

Privileged → DB and storage level access

1️⃣ INTERNET → API GATEWAY
External Entity

User / Browser / API Client

Trust Level: ❌ Untrusted

Data Flow

User sends:

HTTP method

Path

Query parameters

Headers

JWT token

Cookies

JSON body

File stream (if upload)

All fields attacker-controlled.

TRUST BOUNDARY 1

Untrusted Internet → Backend System

At this boundary:

Before:

Identity unknown

Tenant unknown

Role unknown

Intent untrusted

After authentication:

JWT signature validated

user_id extracted

tenant_id resolved server-side

role resolved from DB

request_id generated

Now request becomes:

Partially Trusted (identity trusted, intent not trusted)

2️⃣ API GATEWAY → INTERNAL SERVICES
Process

API Gateway forwards:

Business request

SecurityContext:

user_id

tenant_id

role

request_id

Trust Level: ⚠️ Partially Trusted

User intent still untrusted.

TRUST BOUNDARY 2

Gateway → Internal Services

At this boundary:

Assumptions:

Identity valid

Tenant resolved correctly

Role accurate

Risk:

Services may over-trust context

Missing authz

Missing tenant scoping

3️⃣ INTERNAL SERVICE → AUTHORIZATION SERVICE (gRPC)

When performing sensitive actions:

Project/File Service sends:

user_id

tenant_id

action

resource_id

AuthZ returns:

Allow / Deny

Trust Level:

Internal communication

Must still validate inputs

TRUST BOUNDARY 3

Service → Service (gRPC)

Risk:

AuthZ skipped

Incorrect action names

Wrong tenant_id forwarded

4️⃣ INTERNAL SERVICE → DATABASE (PostgreSQL)

Project/File/Audit Services query:

SELECT with tenant_id

INSERT with tenant_id

UPDATE with tenant_id

DELETE with tenant_id

Data Types:

Project data

File metadata

Tenant data

Audit logs

Trust Level: 🔒 Privileged

TRUST BOUNDARY 4

Service → Database

Risk:

Missing tenant filter

Injection

Overbroad queries

Data leakage

5️⃣ FILE SERVICE → OBJECT STORAGE (MinIO)

File Service performs:

Upload object

Download object

Delete object

Object key format:
tenant/{tenant_id}/project/{project_id}/file/{file_id}

Binary only.

Trust Level: 🔒 Privileged

TRUST BOUNDARY 5

Service → Object Storage

Risk:

Path manipulation

Cross-tenant object access

Exposing internal keys

6️⃣ INTERNAL SERVICES → AUDIT SERVICE

After successful state change:

Service sends:

actor_id

tenant_id

action

resource_id

timestamp

request_id

Audit writes append-only record.

Trust Level: 🔐 Trusted Internal

TRUST BOUNDARY 6

Service → Audit Store

Risk:

Missing audit

Tampered audit

Partial logs

7️⃣ BACKEND → OAUTH PROVIDER

During login:

Gateway redirects user to OAuth provider.

Provider returns:

ID token

Access token

Trust Level: 🌍 External Partially Trusted

TRUST BOUNDARY 7

Backend ↔ External Identity Provider

Risk:

Token misuse

Incorrect issuer validation

Accepting unsigned tokens
